= IO::Redirector

  http://death.rubyforge.org


== DESCRIPTION

A class to redirect $stdout, or other IO object, to a StringIO object,
or any other object with a write() method.


== FEATURES/ISSUES

* ... to be done ...


== RELEASE NOTES

Please see RELEASE file.


== SYNOPSIS

   s = StringIO.new
   r = Redirector.redirect($stdout, s) do
     $stdout.puts "this is a test"
   end


== HOW TO INSTALL

Describe your installation procedure here.

To install with RubyGems simply open a console and type:

  gem install ioredirect

Local installation requires Setup.rb (gem install setup),
then download the tarball package and type:

  tar -xvzf ioredirect-1.0.0.tgz
  cd ioredirect-1.0.0
  sudo setup.rb all

Windows users use 'ruby setup.rb all'.


